Python and Ansible scripts to create hadoop clusters through kamaki API
OS for Ansible server & hadoop nodes: Debian 6.0.7

Prerequisites:
Install Ansible (ansible server) on the machine you want to run the ansible commands (NOT the Hadoop master)

command> python hadoop_cluster.py [options]
see: python hadoop_cluster.py -h

to add new worker node(s):
command> python hadoop_cluster.py [options] --extend

NOTE: You have to manually format the namenode and start the Hadoop cluster
